"If I Understood You, Would I Have This Look on My Face?" - Keep communication as simple and clear as possible! Show empathy, listen to other person- nodding, paraphrasing or understanding from their perspective, Be more expressive and add story
✔️ Connection matters – People engage when you are expressive and relatable.
✔️ Jargon is a barrier – Use analogies and simple words instead.
✔️ Improvisation helps – Being flexible and reading the audience improves communication.
✔️ Storytelling is key – Facts alone aren’t enough; stories create impact.
✔️ Emotional Connection – Why empathy matters in conversations.
